HEADWORD: Larrup
<hw>Lar"rup</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Larruped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Larruping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Perh, a corrupt. of
<ets>lee rope</ets>, used by sailors in beating the boys; but cf. D.
<ets>larpen</ets> to thresh, <ets>larp</ets> a whip, blow.]</ety>
<def>To beat or flog soundly.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Colloq.
U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>Forby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
